events.description: Emperor Petronius Maximus is stoned to death by an angry mob while fleeing Rome.
events.html: • 455 – Emperor Petronius Maximus is stoned to death by an angry mob while fleeing Rome.

events.description: Zhongdu (now Beijing), then under the control of the Jurchen ruler Emperor Xuanzong of Jin, is captured by the Mongols under Genghis Khan, ending the Battle of Zhongdu.
events.html: • 1215 – Zhongdu (now Beijing), then under the control of the Jurchen ruler Emperor Xuanzong of Jin, is captured by the Mongols under Genghis Khan, ending the Battle of Zhongdu.[1]

events.description: Mongol invasion of the Cumans: Battle of the Kalka River: Mongol armies of Genghis Khan led by Subutai defeat Kievan Rus' and Cumans.
events.html: • 1223 – Mongol invasion of the Cumans: Battle of the Kalka River: Mongol armies of Genghis Khan led by Subutai defeat Kievan Rus' and Cumans.

events.description: Mongol invasion of Java was a punitive expedition against King Kertanegara of Singhasari, who had refused to pay tribute to the Yuan and maimed one of its ministers. However, it ended with failure for the Mongols. Regarded as establish City of Surabaya
events.html: • 1293 – Mongol invasion of Java was a punitive expedition against King Kertanegara of Singhasari, who had refused to pay tribute to the Yuan and maimed one of its ministers. However, it ended with failure for the Mongols. Regarded as establish City of Surabaya[2][3]

events.description: King Henry III lays the first stone of the Pont Neuf (New Bridge), the oldest bridge of Paris, France.
events.html: • 1578 – King Henry III lays the first stone of the Pont Neuf (New Bridge), the oldest bridge of Paris, France.[4]

events.description: The pageant London's Love to Prince Henry on the River Thames celebrates the creation of Prince Henry as Prince of Wales.
events.html: • 1610 – The pageant London's Love to Prince Henry on the River Thames celebrates the creation of Prince Henry as Prince of Wales.[5]

events.description: Citing poor eyesight as a reason, Samuel Pepys records the last event in his diary.
events.html: • 1669 – Citing poor eyesight as a reason, Samuel Pepys records the last event in his diary.[6]

events.description: American Revolution: The Mecklenburg Resolves are adopted in the Province of North Carolina.
events.html: • 1775 – American Revolution: The Mecklenburg Resolves are adopted in the Province of North Carolina.[7]

events.description: Manuel Quimper explores the Strait of Juan de Fuca.
events.html: • 1790 – Manuel Quimper explores the Strait of Juan de Fuca.[8]

events.description: The United States enacts its first copyright statute, the Copyright Act of 1790.
events.html: • 1790 – The United States enacts its first copyright statute, the Copyright Act of 1790.

entities.name: Copyright law of the United States

events.description: French Revolution: The Revolutionary Tribunal is suppressed.
events.html: • 1795 – French Revolution: The Revolutionary Tribunal is suppressed.

events.description: French and Spanish forces begin the assault against British forces occupying Diamond Rock, Martinique.
events.html: • 1805 – French and Spanish forces begin the assault against British forces occupying Diamond Rock, Martinique.

events.description: In Australia, William Lawson, Gregory Blaxland and William Wentworth reach Mount Blaxland, effectively marking the end of a route across the Blue Mountains.
events.html: • 1813 – In Australia, William Lawson, Gregory Blaxland and William Wentworth reach Mount Blaxland, effectively marking the end of a route across the Blue Mountains.

events.description: The clock tower at the Houses of Parliament, which houses Big Ben, starts keeping time.
events.html: • 1859 – The clock tower at the Houses of Parliament, which houses Big Ben, starts keeping time.

events.description: American Civil War: Peninsula Campaign: Confederate forces under Joseph E. Johnston and G.W. Smith engage Union forces under George B. McClellan outside the Confederate capital of Richmond, Virginia.
events.html: • 1862 – American Civil War: Peninsula Campaign: Confederate forces under Joseph E. Johnston and G.W. Smith engage Union forces under George B. McClellan outside the Confederate capital of Richmond, Virginia.

events.description: American Civil War: Overland Campaign: Battle of Cold Harbor: The Army of Northern Virginia engages the Army of the Potomac.
events.html: • 1864 – American Civil War: Overland Campaign: Battle of Cold Harbor: The Army of Northern Virginia engages the Army of the Potomac.

events.description: Gilmore's Garden in New York City is renamed Madison Square Garden by William Henry Vanderbilt and is opened to the public at 26th Street and Madison Avenue.
events.html: • 1879 – Gilmore's Garden in New York City is renamed Madison Square Garden by William Henry Vanderbilt and is opened to the public at 26th Street and Madison Avenue.

events.description: The arrival at Plymouth of Tāwhiao, King of Maoris, to claim the protection of Queen Victoria.
events.html: • 1884 – The arrival at Plymouth of Tāwhiao, King of Maoris, to claim the protection of Queen Victoria.

events.description: Johnstown Flood: Over 2,200 people die after a dam fails and sends a 60-foot (18-meter) wall of water over the town of Johnstown, Pennsylvania.
events.html: • 1889 – Johnstown Flood: Over 2,200 people die after a dam fails and sends a 60-foot (18-meter) wall of water over the town of Johnstown, Pennsylvania.

events.description: Second Boer War: The Treaty of Vereeniging ends the war and ensures British control of South Africa.
events.html: • 1902 – Second Boer War: The Treaty of Vereeniging ends the war and ensures British control of South Africa.[9]

events.description: The attempted regicide of Spanish King Alfonso XIII and Queen Victoria Eugenie on their wedding day instead kills 24
events.html: • 1906 – The attempted regicide of Spanish King Alfonso XIII and Queen Victoria Eugenie on their wedding day instead kills 24[10][11]

entities.name: Wedding of King Alfonso XIII and Princess Victoria Eugenie

events.description: The National Negro Committee, forerunner to the National Association for the Advancement of Colored People (NAACP), convenes for the first time.
events.html: • 1909 – The National Negro Committee, forerunner to the National Association for the Advancement of Colored People (NAACP), convenes for the first time.

entities.name: National Association for the Advancement of Colored People

events.description: The South Africa Act comes into force, establishing the Union of South Africa.
events.html: • 1910 – The South Africa Act comes into force, establishing the Union of South Africa.

events.description: The RMS Titanic is launched in Belfast, Northern Ireland.
events.html: • 1911 – The RMS Titanic is launched in Belfast, Northern Ireland.

events.description: The President of Mexico Porfirio Díaz flees the country during the Mexican Revolution.
events.html: • 1911 – The President of Mexico Porfirio Díaz flees the country during the Mexican Revolution.

events.description: World War I: Battle of Jutland: The British Grand Fleet engages the High Seas Fleet in the largest naval battle of the war, which proves indecisive.
events.html: • 1916 – World War I: Battle of Jutland: The British Grand Fleet engages the High Seas Fleet in the largest naval battle of the war, which proves indecisive.

events.description: The Tulsa race massacre kills at least 39, but other estimates of black fatalities vary from 55 to about 300.
events.html: • 1921 – The Tulsa race massacre kills at least 39, but other estimates of black fatalities vary from 55 to about 300.

events.description: Hope Development School fire kills 24 people, mostly disabled children.
events.html: • 1924 – Hope Development School fire kills 24 people, mostly disabled children.[12]

events.description: A 7.7 Mw  earthquake destroys Quetta in modern-day Pakistan killing 40,000.
events.html: • 1935 – A 7.7 Mw  earthquake destroys Quetta in modern-day Pakistan killing 40,000.

events.description: Anglo-Iraqi War: The United Kingdom completes the re-occupation of Iraq and returns 'Abd al-Ilah to power as regent for Faisal II.
events.html: • 1941 – Anglo-Iraqi War: The United Kingdom completes the re-occupation of Iraq and returns 'Abd al-Ilah to power as regent for Faisal II.

events.description: World War II: Imperial Japanese Navy midget submarines begin a series of attacks on Sydney, Australia.
events.html: • 1942 – World War II: Imperial Japanese Navy midget submarines begin a series of attacks on Sydney, Australia.

events.description: Ferenc Nagy, the democratically elected Prime Minister of Hungary, resigns from office after blackmail from the Hungarian Communist Party accusing him of being part of a plot against the state. This grants the Communists effective control of the Hungarian government.
events.html: • 1947 – Ferenc Nagy, the democratically elected Prime Minister of Hungary, resigns from office after blackmail from the Hungarian Communist Party accusing him of being part of a plot against the state. This grants the Communists effective control of the Hungarian government.[13]

events.description: The Uniform Code of Military Justice takes effect as the legal system of the United States Armed Forces.
events.html: • 1951 – The Uniform Code of Military Justice takes effect as the legal system of the United States Armed Forces.[14]

events.description: The U.S. Supreme Court expands on its Brown v. Board of Education decision by ordering district courts and school districts to enforce educational desegregation "at all deliberate speed."
events.html: • 1955 – The U.S. Supreme Court expands on its Brown v. Board of Education decision by ordering district courts and school districts to enforce educational desegregation "at all deliberate speed."[15]

entities.name: Supreme Court of the United States
School integration in the United States

events.description: The South African Constitution of 1961 becomes effective, thus creating the Republic of South Africa, which remains outside the Commonwealth of Nations until 1 June 1994, when South Africa is returned to Commonwealth membership.
events.html: • 1961 – The South African Constitution of 1961 becomes effective, thus creating the Republic of South Africa, which remains outside the Commonwealth of Nations until 1 June 1994, when South Africa is returned to Commonwealth membership.

events.description: In Moscow City Court, the Rokotov–Faibishenko show trial begins, despite the Khrushchev Thaw to reverse Stalinist elements in Soviet society.
events.html: • 1961 – In Moscow City Court, the Rokotov–Faibishenko show trial begins, despite the Khrushchev Thaw to reverse Stalinist elements in Soviet society.

events.description: The West Indies Federation dissolves.
events.html: • 1962 – The West Indies Federation dissolves.

events.description: The 7.9 Mw  Ancash earthquake shakes Peru with a maximum Mercalli intensity of VIII (Severe) and a landslide buries the town of Yungay, Peru. Between 66,794 and 70,000 were killed and 50,000 were injured.
events.html: • 1970 – The 7.9 Mw  Ancash earthquake shakes Peru with a maximum Mercalli intensity of VIII (Severe) and a landslide buries the town of Yungay, Peru. Between 66,794 and 70,000 were killed and 50,000 were injured.

events.description: In accordance with the Uniform Monday Holiday Act passed by the U.S. Congress in 1968, observation of Memorial Day occurs on the last Monday in May for the first time, rather than on the traditional Memorial Day of May 30.
events.html: • 1971 – In accordance with the Uniform Monday Holiday Act passed by the U.S. Congress in 1968, observation of Memorial Day occurs on the last Monday in May for the first time, rather than on the traditional Memorial Day of May 30.

events.description: The United States Senate votes to cut off funding for the bombing of Khmer Rouge targets within Cambodia, hastening the end of the Cambodian Civil War.
events.html: • 1973 – The United States Senate votes to cut off funding for the bombing of Khmer Rouge targets within Cambodia, hastening the end of the Cambodian Civil War.

events.description: Indian Airlines Flight 440 crashes near Palam Airport in Delhi, killing 48.
events.html: • 1973 – Indian Airlines Flight 440 crashes near Palam Airport in Delhi, killing 48.[16]

events.description: The Trans-Alaska Pipeline System is completed.
events.html: • 1977 – The Trans-Alaska Pipeline System is completed.

events.description: United States–Canada tornado outbreak: Forty-one tornadoes hit Ohio, Pennsylvania, New York, and Ontario, leaving 76 dead.
events.html: • 1985 – United States–Canada tornado outbreak: Forty-one tornadoes hit Ohio, Pennsylvania, New York, and Ontario, leaving 76 dead.

events.description: Bicesse Accords in Angola lay out a transition to multi-party democracy under the supervision of the United Nations' UNAVEM II peacekeeping mission.
events.html: • 1991 – Bicesse Accords in Angola lay out a transition to multi-party democracy under the supervision of the United Nations' UNAVEM II peacekeeping mission.

entities.name: United Nations Angola Verification Mission II

events.description: Air France retires its fleet of Concorde aircraft.
events.html: • 2003 – Air France retires its fleet of Concorde aircraft.[17]

events.description: Vanity Fair reveals that Mark Felt was "Deep Throat".
events.html: • 2005 – Vanity Fair reveals that Mark Felt was "Deep Throat".

events.description: Usain Bolt breaks the world record in the 100m sprint, with a wind-legal (+1.7 m/s) 9.72 seconds
events.html: • 2008 – Usain Bolt breaks the world record in the 100m sprint, with a wind-legal (+1.7 m/s) 9.72 seconds

events.description: Israeli Shayetet 13 commandos boarded the Gaza Freedom Flotilla while still in international waters trying to break the ongoing blockade of the Gaza Strip; nine Turkish citizens on the flotilla were killed in the ensuing violent affray.
events.html: • 2010 – Israeli Shayetet 13 commandos boarded the Gaza Freedom Flotilla while still in international waters trying to break the ongoing blockade of the Gaza Strip; nine Turkish citizens on the flotilla were killed in the ensuing violent affray.

events.description: The asteroid 1998 QE2 and its moon make their closest approach to Earth for the next two centuries.
events.html: • 2013 – The asteroid 1998 QE2 and its moon make their closest approach to Earth for the next two centuries.

entities.name: List of asteroid close approaches to Earth

events.description: A record breaking 2.6 mile wide tornado strikes near El Reno, Oklahoma, United States, causing eight fatalities (including three storm chasers) and over 150 injuries.
events.html: • 2013 – A record breaking 2.6 mile wide tornado strikes near El Reno, Oklahoma, United States, causing eight fatalities (including three storm chasers) and over 150 injuries.

events.description: Syrian civil war: The Syrian Democratic Forces (SDF) launch the Manbij offensive, in order to capture the city of Manbij from the Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant (ISIL).
events.html: • 2016 – Syrian civil war: The Syrian Democratic Forces (SDF) launch the Manbij offensive, in order to capture the city of Manbij from the Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant (ISIL).[18][19][20][21]

entities.name: Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant

events.html: • 2017 – A car bomb explodes in a crowded intersection in Kabul near the German embassy during rush hour, killing over 90 and injuring 463.
